                      lines can affect the refrigerator’s performance. Most ice
                      makers are dependent on a steady supply of water to
                      function correctly.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Dirty Condenser Coils: </b>Dust and debris on the
                      condenser coils can prevent your refrigerator from cooling
                      efficiently. Cleaning the coils with soapy water can often
                      fix this issue.
                    </li>
                    <li>
