                      or in the freezer compartment can cause strange noises. To
                      fix this, turn off the refrigerator and use a hair dryer
                      to carefully melt the ice. Be sure to place a towel or
                      container to catch any water that melts off.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Loose Components: </b>Over time, screws and other
                      components inside the refrigerator can become loose. Check
                      for loose parts and tighten them if necessary. This is a
                      straightforward job that can prevent further noise issues.
                    </li>
                    <li>
