                <div class="questions">
                  <p>
                    There could be several reasons why your refrigerator's ice
                    maker is not working. Here are some common issues to
                    consider:
                  </p>

                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      <b>Water Supply Issues: </b>Ensure that the water supply
                      line is connected properly and that the water valve is
                      turned on. A kinked or clogged supply line can prevent
                      water from reaching the ice maker.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Frozen Water Line: </b>Sometimes the water line inside
                      the freezer can freeze, blocking the flow of water.
                      Thawing the line may resolve this issue.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Faulty Water Inlet Valve: </b>The water inlet valve
                      controls the flow of water to the ice maker. If it's
                      defective or clogged, the ice maker won't receive water.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Ice Maker Control Arm: </b>Check if the control arm
                      (the metal bar that moves up and down) is in the off
                      position. If it's stuck in the up position, it will
                      prevent the ice maker from making ice.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Temperature Settings: </b>Ensure your freezer is set to
                      the correct temperature. If it's too warm, it may prevent
                      the ice maker from working properly. The ideal freezer
                      temperature is typically between 0°F and 5°F (-18°C to
                      -15°C).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Clogged or Dirty Filter: </b>A clogged water filter can
                      restrict water flow to the ice maker. Check and replace
                      the filter if necessary.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Ice Maker Assembly Issues: </b>Mechanical or electrical
                      issues within the ice maker assembly, such as a faulty
                      motor, thermostat, or control module, can also cause
                      problems.
