                  </p>

                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      <b>Check the Power Supply: </b>Ensure that your
                      refrigerator is properly plugged in and that the outlet is
                      functioning correctly. Sometimes, a faulty power supply
                      can cause clicking noises.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Inspect the Condenser and Evaporator Fans: </b>These
                      fans help circulate air within the refrigerator. If
                      they’re obstructed or malfunctioning, they can produce
                      clicking sounds. Ensure they are free from debris and
                      functioning properly.
                    </li>
                    <li>
